task.summary: Default task
Initial commit of all Laravel files, and the beginning of the API authentication layer.
DEV-72 #comment * Finalized authentication user & user IP table. * Added User and UserIp models.

DEV-72 #comment * Added exception handler to properly handle exceptions via encoding. * Added test ping route & controller action. * Added session storage of "user" during the duration of their stay ;) * Added encoding to the api user model. * CrewkieApi\Response class added to handle responses properly. * Default connection is set to the API database. * Added migrations for all relevant tables. * Updated readme with information regarding how to set-up DBs and use migrations.
DEV-72 #comment * Updated authenticate to update the latestauth_at field when authenticated.
DEV-72 #comment * Fixed User Model and removed timestamps reference.
DEV-72 #comment * Added Ping action.

DEV-79 #comment * Added $apiResponse class to the authenticate method. * Removed CSRF protection. Unnecessary for this type of RESTful API layer. * Added the Request layer. * Added ERROR_CODE_BADREQUEST to the Response layer.

DEV-79 #comment * Added Request to the Abstract Controller. * Request Layer improvement. * Added magic resolution based on returning a string from private method that defines available methods (for insight purposes).

DEV-31 #comment * Added CrewkieApi\Http\Controllers\GameAccountController and routing for it. * GameAccount Model has been added. Still a WIP. Plans to add validation and constraints globally are in progress. * game/account route added. * Default config/database.php updated with game connection definition.
DEV-79 #comment Added the ability to find game account by ID, username, and/or password.
DEV-83 #comment Added game/account/encryptpassword to properly encrypt a password.
DEV-79 #comment Fixed fatal bug where apiUrl would consistenly add-on to itself during call of methods.
DEV-79 #comment Fixed issue with authenticate error code.
DEV-79 #comment Removed cURL options.

DEV-97 #comment * Added caching concepts. * Added Timeclock method to find and search as well as cache on a 30-minute rotation. * Added Account and Character models. * Updated Request layer with new API method.
Logging of errors enabled for cURL.

Fixed timeclock to pull data and desc by start_date.
